\subsection{Further notation}

We denote the conditional probabilities by:
\begin{align*}
\eta_y(x)&:\mathbb{P}[Y1|Xx]\\
\eta_a(x)&:\mathbb{P}[A1|Xx]
\end{align*}

And we use the following abbreviations for simplicity:
\begin{align*}
   \mathbb{P}_{D}&:\mathbb{P}_{(x,a,y)\sim D}\\
   \mathbb{P}^+_D(f) &: \mathbb{P}_{D}[\sign(f(x))1]\\
   \mathbb{P}^-_D(f) &: \mathbb{P}_{D}[\sign(f(x))0]
\end{align*}

Finally we denote the base rates by:
\begin{align*}
\pi_{\cdot,y}&:\mathbb{P}[Y1]\\
\pi_{a,\cdot}&:\mathbb{P}[A1]\\
\pi_{a,y}&:\mathbb{P}[A1,Y1]
\end{align*}
